    "body": "When Spack is used on shared systems, the cache directories are by default world- and group- readable, even when the `packages.py` restricts the permissions of the installed modulefile and prefix.\r\n\r\nThis is something of a \"straw man\" PR since I'm not sure it's the best (least intrusive) way to make the changes, so I'd be happy for any suggestions of how to change it.\r\n\r\nResolves #13784.",
